IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: THE MISSION OF THE LEADERSHIP NORTH CAROLINA PROGRAM IS TO INFORM, DEVELOP AND ENGAGE COMMITTED LEADERS BY BROADENING THEIR UNDERSTANDING OF AND INVOLVEMENT IN ISSUES AND OPPORTUNITIES FACING OUR STATE.
IRS990.MissionDesc: THE MISSION OF THE LEADERSHIP NORTH CAROLINA PROGRAM IS TO INFORM, DEVELOP AND ENGAGE COMMITTED LEADERS BY BROADENING THEIR UNDERSTANDING OF AND INVOLVEMENT IN ISSUES AND OPPORTUNITIES FACING OUR STATE.
IRS990.Desc: SEVEN MONTHLY, TWO-DAY SESSIONS GIVE CLASS MEMBERS A BROADER UNDERSTANDING OF THE STATE WITH A FOCUS ON ISSUES IN TOPICAL AREAS OF ECONOMIC DEVELOPMENT, EDUCATION, ENVIRONMENT, GOVERNMENT/POLITICS, AND HEALTH AND HUMAN SERVICES. 55 STUDENTS ATTENDED THE COURSES IN 2017/2018 YEAR.IN ADDITION TO THE STUDENTS, 762 ATTENDEES WENT TO CLASS XXIV SESSIONS AND 180 ATTENDED LNC FORUM SESSIONS TO FURTHER AWARENESS OF THE ISSUES FACED BY THE STATE OF NORTH CAROLINA. 7 TOTAL LEADERSHIP SESSIONS AND EVENTS WERE HELD DURING THE YEAR. IN KIND CONTRIBUTIONS WERE $28,887 FOR OFFICE SPACE RENT AND $5,315 FOR MARKETING AND ADVERTISING EXPENSE.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE STANLEY FRANK ENDOWMENT FUND IS UTILIZED TO PROVIDE SUPPORT FOR AWARDS. WILLIAM GARRETT FUND IS A BOARD DESIGNATED FUND WHICH HAS A PRIMARY PURPOSE OF PROVIDING SCHOLARSHIP AID TO PROSPECTIVE PARTICIPANTS WHO APPLY FOR SCHOLARSHIP ASSISTANCE. THE MAJOR DONOR TO THE LEGACY FUND RESTICTED USE OF THE FUNDS TO PROVIDE SUPPORT AND SPONSORSHIP TO LEADERSHIP NORTH CAROLINA HEALTH AND HUMAN SERVICES SESSION.

THE INTERNAL REVENUE SERVICE HAS DETERMINED THAT THE ORGANIZATION IS EXEMPT FROM FEDERAL INCOME TAXATION AS AN ORGANIZATION DESCRIBED IN SECTION 501(C)(3) OF THE INTERNAL REVENUE CODE (IRC). THE ORGANIZATION IS EXEMPT FROM FEDERAL INCOME TAX UNDER SECTION 501(C)(3) OF THE IRC. THE ORGANIZATION ACCOUNTS FOR UNCERTAIN INCOME TAX POSITIONS BY PRESCRIBING A MINIMUM PROBABILITY THRESHOLD A TAX POSITION MUST MEET BEFORE A FINANCIAL STATEMENT INCOME TAX BENEFIT IS RECOGNIZED. THE MINIMUM THRESHOLD IS DEFINED AS A TAX POSITION, BASED SOLELY ON ITS TECHNICAL MERITS, THAT WOULD MORE LIKELY THAN NOT BE SUSTAINED UPON EXAMINATION BY THE RELEVANT TAX AUTHORITY WITH KNOWLEDGE OF THE SAME FACTS. THE TAX BENEFIT TO BE RECOGNIZED IS MEASURED AS THE LARGEST AMOUNT OF BENEFIT THAT IS GREATER THAN 50% LIKELY OF BEING REALIZED UPON ULTIMATE RESOLUTION. BASED ON ALL KNOWN FACTS AND CIRCUMSTANCES AND CURRENT TAX LAW, THE ORGANIZATION BELIEVES THE TOTAL AMOUNT OF UNCERTAIN INCOME TAX POSITION LIABILITIES AND RELATED ACCRUED INTEREST ARE NOT MATERIAL TO ITS FINANCIAL POSITION. AS OF JUNE 30, 2018 AND INCLUDING THE PREVIOUS THREE YEARS CONSIDERING EXTENSIONS, THE ORGANIZATION'S INCOME TAX RETURNS ARE OPEN AND SUBJECT TO EXAMINATION BY TAX AUTHORITIES WITH RELEVANT JURISDICTION. SHOULD SUCH AN EXAMINATION TAKE PLACE, MANAGEMENT DOES NOT ANTICIPATE ANY SIGNIFICANT ISSUES RELATED TO THE OPEN YEARS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 2
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION'S OFFICERS AND DIRECTORS ARE LEADERS IN THE STATE OF NORTH CAROLINA AND HOLD POLITICAL OFFICES, EXECUTIVE POSITIONS WITH COMPANIES AND ARE BUSINESS OWNERS. AT TIMES DURING THE FISCAL YEAR, DIRECTORS MAY ENGAGE IN BUSINESS RELATIONSHIPS WITH EACH OTHER.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: PRIOR TO FILING THE 990 EXEMPT ORGANIZATION RETURN, THE ORGANIZATION PROVIDES A COPY OF THE RETURN TO THE GOVERNING BOARD AND ITS COMMITTEE THAT IS DELEGATED THE POWER TO APPROVE THE 990 EXEMPT ORGANIZATION RETURN ON BEHALF OF THE GOVERNING BOARD.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12C
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: ON ANNUAL BASIS IN THE FALL BOARD MEETING, EACH BOARD MEMBER REVIEWS THE CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY AND SIGNS THAT THEY HAVE RECEIVED, UNDERSTAND AND AGREES TO THE POLICY. IF A CONFLICT IS DETERMINED, IT IS RECORDED IN THE MINUTES OF THE MEETING.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 15
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE COMPENSATION COMMITTEE HAS AN ANNUAL REVIEW OF THE PRESIDENT'S COMPENSATION. THE PRESIDENT SUBMITS GOALS FOR UPCOMING YEAR FOR CONSIDERATION AND A SELF ASSESSMENT NARRATIVE IS PROVIDED BY THE PRESIDENT WITH RESULTS FROM GOALS IN THE PAST PRIOR YEAR. COMPENSATION COMMITTEE UTILIZES DATA FROM EITHER NC CENTER FOR NON PROFITS SALARY SURVEY AND/OR THE ASSOCIATION OF EXECUTIVE DATABASE.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION MAKES ITS GOVERNING DOCUMENTS, CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY AND FINANCIAL STATEMENTS AVAILABLE TO THE PUBLIC AT THE PUBLIC'S REQUEST.
